Gazprom, Raspadskaya, Surgutneftegas: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 
2011-04-11T20:01:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/gazprom-raspadskaya-surgutneftegas-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  The 30-stock Micex Index fell 0.6 percent to 1,845.78,
while the dollar-denominated RTS Index slid 0.5 percent to
2,113.55.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX): Russia’s gas export monopoly shipped
almost 30 percent more gas abroad in the first quarter as prices
rose on unrest in  Libya  and  Japan ’s worst earthquake on record.
Gazprom added 0.3 percent to 243.93 rubles.  OAO  Raspadskaya (RASP)  : The Russian producer of coal for
steelmaking may report its 2010 financial results. Raspadskaya
fell 0.9 percent to 202.20 rubles.  OAO Surgutneftegas (SNGS RX): Oil fell from a 30-month high
after the  International Monetary Fund  cut its growth forecasts
for the U.S. and Japan. Surgutneftegas, a Russian oil producer,
fell 0.4 percent to 31.378 rubles.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at 
 ajordan11@bloomberg.net . 